<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><Document xmlns="http://www.ortodokskoptik.id/BukuBacaanKoptik">   <Season id="JoyousSaturday">      <Comment>         <Language id="English">            <ol>               <li>At the end of the service, Psalm 150 is not chanted, but the Psalm and Gospel for the Distribution are read.</li>               <li>The hymn “My God My God (<span class="Coptic">Panou] Panou]</span>)” is chanted in the tune of the great "The Grace of Our Lord (<span class="Coptic">Pih~mot gar</span>)" or "The Love of God (<span class="Coptic">? a~gap/</span>)"</li>            </ol>          </Language>                  </Comment>            <Role id="Reader">         <Comment>            <Language id="English">               The Psalm is chanted half in the Paschal “Edreebe” tune, and the other half in the standard tune.            </Language>         </Comment>                  <Section expanded="true">            <Title>               <Language id="English">Psalm 68: 1</Language>               <Language id="Arabic">مزامير 68: 1</Language>            </Title>                     <InsertDocument path="pascha/include/PsalmOfDavid"/>            <BibleReference reference="Psalms 68:1" hideIntroConclusion="true"/>                     </Section>      </Role>            <InsertDocument path="pascha/include/KeEperto"/>            <Role id="Reader">         <Comment>            <Language id="English">               The Gospel is read, the first half in Paschal tune and the second half in annual tune.            </Language>            <Language id="Arabic">               ويقرأ الانجيل نصفه بلحن الحزن والنصف الآخر بالطريقة السنوية.            </Language>         </Comment>                  <BibleReference reference="Luke 24:1-12" type="section"/>      </Role>            <InsertDocument path="include/PanotiPanoti"/>            <Comment>         <Language id="English">            If the Distribution is not finished, the prophesies of Eve of the Resurrection are read.